        "title": "fix: prepare scoped npm release",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move npm distribution to `@steipete/mcp-agentify` while retaining the `mcp-agentify` executable.\n- Replace legacy JSON-RPC framing with the official MCP SDK and dynamically discover backend tools.\n- Package and harden the localhost dashboard, including lifecycle handling and credential redaction.\n- Add current provider examples, release documentation, package validation, integration coverage, and Node.js CI.\n\n## Package identity\n\nThe existing [`mcp-agentify@1.0.0`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/mcp-agentify) is unrelated and points to [`me-saurabhkohli/agentify`](https://github.com/me-saurabhkohli/agentify). Authenticated npm identity is `steipete`; [`@steipete/mcp-agentify`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@steipete/mcp-agentify) is publicly absent. No registry publish was attempted.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `npm run format:check`\n- `npm run lint`\n- `npx tsc --noEmit`\n- `npm test` (34 tests)\n- `npm run check:package`\n- `npm audit --omit=dev` (0 vulnerabilities)\n- Autoreview clean with no accepted/actionable findings\n- Fresh exact tarball installed and live-tested with real OpenAI, filesystem MCP, packaged dashboard, and Browserbase start/navigate/extract/end\n- Live config, logs, traces, stderr, and responses scanned for provider credential values: none found\n\n## Release plan\n\nVersion intentionally remains `0.1.0`; version changes happen only during an explicit release. After merge, verify npm scope ownership again, publish `@steipete/mcp-agentify@0.1.0` with public access, create the matching Git tag and GitHub Release, verify registry metadata/tarball/integrity/publish time, then add the next patch `Unreleased` closeout.\n",
